<h2 class="bold font-l">Code Red Situation</h2>
<p class="_pmvv-vidbox-descTxt">
Charles Xavier attempts to enforce a lockdown to break Erik Lehnsherr out of a government prison. When it's obvious that it's not working, Logan decides to take a more direct approach. </p>
<p class='example_row'>Example of:<br><a href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BavarianFireDrill" class='trope-example-link'>Bavarian Fire Drill</a></p>
</div>
<div class="video-examples-thumbs">
<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="h6vgcv" data-video-descrip="X-Men: Days of Future Past, features the classic Quicksilver scene, in which he saves Xavier, Erik &amp;amp; Logan with his super speed, making everything seem like its in slow motion. All set to Jim Croce's Time in a Bottle." data-video-title="Time in a Bottle" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/h6vgcv_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/h6vgcv.jpg" data-video-trope="Main/BulletTime" data-video-tropename="Bullet Time" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="" data-video-rating-count="" data-video-media-sources="Film/XMenDaysOfFuturePast" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link video-background-image lazy-image" data-src="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/h6vgcv.jpg">
<p><span class="bold">Time in a Bottle</span></p>
</a>
